		<b>Comment By Bill, 4-17-08</b>
		<p>I lived on the Hill in a home rented by Mark Alexander a Denver attorney...several of us including a decendant of James J Hill the founder of the Northern Pacific RR..it was on Euclid near Beach Park on either 10th or 12th...who knows  :) ...soon as I moved in there was a speech by SI Hayakawa at Macky and the Denver Panthers tore the place up.. and of course the obligatory trips back home to Illinois or San Francisco in my VW bus..in any case its difficult to describe those times in Boulder or Berkeley or anywhere in the USA...as Pete Seeger says.."wasn't that a time" its almost 40 yrs on and many of us would like to find someone in our memories from those days and ask..."what did you feel.."  "wasnt that a time"....  I know every generation has their radical this or that or own special memories but those of us going through all that in Boulder in the late 60's have a unique perspective/reason to say " Wow"......</p>
		
