		<b>Comment By Joe the Stoner, 3-01-09</b>
		<p>On any given day (except maybe cold and snowy days) you may see one or two legitimate hippies walking down Pearl Street in downtown Boulder, or see the remnants of Boulder's past by visiting Nederland, a small hippie mountain community just a short drive up the mountain from Boulder, a straight shot up Canyon Blvd.<br />
<br />
While there are many select "rich folks" in Boulder, there is also a growing "Neo-Hippies of the 21st century" group of people living in South Boulder.  The movement is growing still today.  As a matter of fact, I myself, Joe the Stoner, am a part of this neo-hippie group.  Please visit <a href="http://www.newwest.net/?URL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.joethestoner.com">http://www.joethestoner.com</a> for more information.  An Official "420 friendly" website.</p>
		
